❗We strongly object to the words of Ms. Elvira Niewiera spoken during the Polish-German Forum held in @PLinDeutschland.

Ms. Niewiera, a director, screenwriter and social activist claimed that the IPN President Karol Nawrocki would not have won the presidential election without the support of Russian propaganda.

Such statements are untrue, hurtful, shocking and outrageous. Since the Russian Federation's aggression against Ukraine in February 2022, thanks to the efforts of the IPN and local authorities, more than 40 out of the 60 objects glorifying the Red Army terror have been removed from public space. For these actions, the IPN Head Karol Nawrocki was included in the list of persons wanted by the Russian Federation authorities. So were many other public figures, including Estonia's Prime Minister Kaja Kallas. 

❗The notion that the Kremlin could support Karol Nawrocki's presidential campaign in any way is absurd.

@MSZ_RP
